<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-317-647  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 317 647.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Feb 6 1989 v6 n5 p70(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A menace to society. (computer viruses)</TITLE><AUTHOR>DiDio, Laura.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Industry experts in security and computer viruses worry that thenext major virus will cost lives, not simply dollars or downtime.andO;Most viruses, worms, Trojan Horses and logic bombs have been doneby students and hackers to gain notoriety, but a virus could alsobe used as a terrorist tactic .andP;  Potential targets of computerviruses are airports, hospitals, or phone and power companies.andO;There is no way to prevent or defend against a virus penetration.andO;Legislation has been introduced, but it is expected to act only asa deterrent, not eliminate viruses.andP;  Most users are reluctant tosay if their companies have been attacked by a virus or whatprecautions they take.andP;  Users have three choices in dealing withcomputer viruses: stop sharing information, install viralprotection packages or use common sense and practice good computerhygiene.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer VirusesComputer CrimesSabotageVandalismData SecuritySecurity Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>